The defendant Lisa J Patten was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Reserve Judge Neal Nettesheim presiding for Branch II:

[MA]Case called at 2:12pm
Defendant Lisa J Patten in court, in custody with Attorney Steven John Luchsinger.  Brookellen Teuber appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  
The Court reviews the Criminal Case Settlement form with Ms.Patten , verifying that she understands and joins in the agreement. 

Constitutional rights reviewed; maximum penalties recited; plea of " GUILTY  " entered; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts the plea, finds Ms. Patten  guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

Sentencing arguments given by Counsel
--ADA Teuber submits victim impact statement; Court reviews
--ADA Teuber notes victims are present in Courtroom

Statement made by Ms. Patten

The Court sentences Ms. Patten   to  8  years, with an Initial Term of Confinement in Prison of  3  years, and the maximum time to serve on Extended Supervision of  5 years.  This sentence is to be served concurrent to sentence in being.

The Court finds that the Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program "Boot Camp".
The Court finds that the Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

The Court gives  0   days credit for time already served.

The Court orders as conditions of Extended Supervision:
--to submit to AODA assessment and follow through with treatment recommendations per Agent
--maintain absolute sobriety
--not to consume alcohol
--not to consume controlled substance without valid prescription
--take all prescription drugs as prescribed
--random drug and/or alcohol screening
--to attempt to obtain/maintain employment and/or education program per Agent
--no contact with any known drug offender except for treatment purposes as deemed appropriate per Agent
--to comply with DNA sample provision upon demand
--to pay costs, fees, assessments and surcharges including the DNA surcharge

Felony Firearm and Voting-rights prohibitions/warnings given
